script:
The bar chart demonstrates population distribution in Australia in 2016 by age group and gender,

Including ages from 1 to 100, measured in thousands.

According to the age group, people aged 25 to 34 had the highest number,

that is nearly 700 thousand.

However, those aged 90 to 100 had the lowest number,

that is nearly 10 thousand.

Besides, there is another data such as ages 1 to 14,

that is nearly 600 thousand.

In general, there is a big difference in population distribution by age group and gender in Australia.
